{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"readerLock","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_rw_lock_reader_lock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" while the current thread already"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"owns a write lock leads to undefined behaviour. Read locks however"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can be taken recursively, in which case you need to make sure to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_rw_lock_reader_unlock()"},{"text":" the same amount of times.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is implementation-defined how many read locks are allowed to be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"held on the same lock simultaneously. If the limit is hit,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or if a deadlock is detected, a critical warning will be emitted.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/readerlock()"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerLock()"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"readerLock()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerLock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:4GLib14RWLockProtocolPAAE10readerLockyyF"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Obtain a read lock on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"text":". If another thread currently holds","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":", the current thread will block until the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"write lock was (held and) released. If another thread does not hold","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the write lock, but is waiting for it, it is implementation defined","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the reader or writer will block. Read locks can be taken","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recursively."}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Mutex":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mutex","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Mutex","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" struct is an opaque data structure to represent a mutex","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(mutual exclusion). It can be used to protect data against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"access."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Mutex"}],"title":"Mutex"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RWLockProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The GRWLock struct is an opaque data structure to represent a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reader-writer lock. It is similar to a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"text":" in that it allows","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multiple threads to coordinate access to a shared resource.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol","type":"topic","title":"RWLockProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RWLockProtocol/readerLock()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RWLockProtocol\/readerLock()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"readerLock"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Obtain a read lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":". If another thread currently holds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the write lock on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rwLock"},{"type":"text","text":", the current thread will block until the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"write lock was (held and) released. If another thread does not hold","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the write lock, but is waiting for it, it is implementation defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whether the reader or writer will block. Read locks can be taken"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recursively.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/rwlockprotocol\/readerlock()","role":"symbol","title":"readerLock()","type":"topic"}}}